cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.THEORY, cs.DS, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the interpretation of higher-order stateful concurrent programs using event structures, which is a topic closely related to logic and semantics. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the interpretation of a programming language (Idealized Parallel Algol) in the constructed cartesian closed category. 
- cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science) is another possible category as the paper presents a new category (CHO) based on event structures and expands on the existing category (TCG) to interpret concurrent programs. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the construction of a category based on event structures, which can be seen as a type of data structure. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the interpretation of concurrent programs, which is a topic relevant to software engineering.
